\noindent\textbf{individual next-generation intelligent computer system}


\large
$\Rightarrow$
\normalsize
\textit{features}\textasteriskcentered:
\begin{flushright}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textit{individual next-generation computer
system cannot be decomposed into subsystems that can be developed absolutely independently of each other and coordinated only by inputs and outputs, implementing the "black box" principle.}
        \item In an \textit{individual next-generation intelligent computer system}, \uline{convergence}, compatibility and "meaningful" interaction of various types of knowledge and models of problem solving are necessary. That is, an \textit{individual next-generation intelligent computer system} should be a \textit{hybrid system}.
    \end{itemize}
\end{flushright}


